                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;What you call &quot;transformation or translation&quot; is usually called &lt;i&gt;interpolation.&lt;/i&gt; The expression &lt;code&gt;&apos;foo $bar baz&apos;&lt;/code&gt; is simply the literal string &lt;code&gt;foo $bar baz&lt;/code&gt; whereas &lt;code&gt;&quot;foo $bar baz&quot;&lt;/code&gt; interpolates the value of the variable &lt;code&gt;bar&lt;/code&gt; into the string between the literal symbols &lt;code&gt;foo&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;baz&lt;/code&gt; with spaces in between.&lt;/span&gt;

